The paper discusses privacy and security issues related to MAC address randomization in mobile devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also analyzes the implementation of randomization techniques by different operating systems, manufacturers, and models of devices, which could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper identifies flaws in the existing randomization techniques, which could be considered as a study of operating systems (cs.OS).
